	   <a name=104361572213119></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104361572213119><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=104361572213119>RE: Advice for type of weapon?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=104361572213119#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=204838><span id= >plumnilly</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jan 26th 4:44 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As a shaman, you can keep two skills maxxed. I suggest pierce (epic) and 1HB. I know the damage is higher per hit with 2HB, but if you whiff it's a long time between whacks, The trick is using the Fleeting Fury line of spells. Keep dex buff on at all times, cast Fleeting Fury (or its successors) at least once during the fight. You can maxx two skills from about 6 on. The other reason for 1HB is the shield, Charred Guardian Shield is nice AC and +9 wis. There are others in the game now that make it look like newbie gear.<br><br>Hardar 30 shaman Lanys T'vyl<br>&nbsp;<br>The only difference between a rut and a grave is depth.</td></tr>
